==English==
===Noun===
'''multi-level marketing''' 
# [[Business]] [[system]] where [[goods]] and [[services]] are sold through a [[pyramid]] [[structure]], with [[distributor]]s on the top supplying others lower down the [[scale]] in return for [[commission]].
===Adjective===
# The term is sometimes used as an adjective, as...
#: A '''multi-level marketing''' meeting will take place next week.
===Note===
Multi-level marketing is considered a [[legitimate]] business if the [[emphasis]] is primarily on the sale of products or service.  See related terms for details of [[illegal]] schemes that rely heavily on [[recruitment]] of new [[investor]]s to make money.
